quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Image Slider[/h1]

Now we need to handle the Next and Prev button clicks and call the corresponding functions to change the image.
[b]HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<div>
  <button [b]onclick="prev()"[/b]> Prev </button>
  <img id="slider" src="http://www.sololearn.com/uploads/slider/1.jpg" 
    width="200px" height="100px"/>
  <button [b]onclick="next()"[/b]> Next </button>
</div>[/code]
[b] JS:[/b] [code format="js" codeId="955"]  var images = [
  "http://www.sololearn.com/uploads/slider/1.jpg", 
  "http://www.sololearn.com/uploads/slider/2.jpg", 
  "http://www.sololearn.com/uploads/slider/3.jpg"
  ];
  var num = 0;

function [b]next[/b]() {
  var slider = document.getElementById("slider");
  num++;
  if(num >= images.length) {
    num = 0;
  }
  slider.src = images[num];
  }

function [b]prev[/b]() {
  var slider = document.getElementById("slider");
  num--;
  if(num < 0) {
    num = images.length-1;
  }
  slider.src = images[num];
}[/code]
The [b]num [/b]variable holds the current image. The next and previous button clicks are handled by their corresponding functions, which change the source of the image to the next/previous image in the array.
[note]We have created a functioning image slider![/note]
